        <section class="project__group">
            <header>
                <h3>The Mosby Design System</h3>
                <p>Given past experiences with systems work at Dow Jones, one of my first tasks at Total Expert was to migrate the current library of application assets from Sketch over to Figma. Given the ehancements to component architecture that the latter supports, this required building components from the ground up. This also allowed us to refine the markup and styles that support each of these components along the way.</p>
                <p><strong>Project Responsibilities</strong><br>UX/UI Design, Systems Engineer, Front-End Development, Documentation and Best Practices</p>
            </header>

            <figure class="width--sm">
                <img loading="lazy" class="border shadow--generic" src="public/img/work/mosby/mosby-hero.jpg" alt="A stylized crop of an assortment of multi-select dropdown menus, all with a small amount of deviation from one another.">
            </figure>
            
            <p>It's a necessary evil to outline all the possible edge cases that a particular component like the multi-select dropdown can offer. In this case the multi-select dropdown can be presented in one of nine different ways. My responsibility with the design system was to ensure all nine of those deviations all presented themselves to the end user in the same manner on screen.</p>
            
            <figure>
                <img loading="lazy" class="border shadow--generic" src="public/img/work/mosby/mosby-components.jpg" alt="An organized collection of various design components commonly used for web development, including buttons, input fields, icons, and menus.">
            </figure>
            
            <section class="project__group">
                <header>
                    <h4>Documentation</h4>
                    <p>Nobody wakes up in the morning excited to write documentation, but an accessible style guide is an important asset when creating any system. These guidelines allow for flexible usage given the circumstance while still feeling like part of a larger, more cohesive whole. Visual aids for what should and shouldn't be done for each situation aids in the understanding of how best to incorporate items.</p>
                </header>
            </section>
            
            <figure class="grid grid--3 width--sm ">
